.Dd April 28, 2026
.Dt DWELL 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm dwell
.Nd demonstrate APSIS in-process variable sampling
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Fl -demo
.Op Fl r Ar rules.trip
.Nm
.Fl h | -help
.Nm
.Fl -version
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
runs a tiny in-process sampler demonstration.
.Pp
For production use, include
.In apsis.h ,
initialize an
.Vt apsis_dwell_ctx ,
register variables with
.Fn apsis_dwell_watch_* ,
and call
.Fn apsis_dwell_tick
at explicit sampling points in the program.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width "--demo"
.It Fl -demo
Run the demonstration sampler.
.It Fl r Ar path , Fl -rules Ar path
Use a rules file for the demonstration.
If omitted,
.Nm
installs a built-in rule for
.Ar worker.queue.depth .
.It Fl h , Fl -help
Show usage.
.It Fl -version
Show version.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Nm
returns 0 when the demonstration runs without emitting an event, 1 when an
event is emitted, and 2 for usage or rule-loading errors.
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bd -literal -offset indent
dwell --demo
dwell --demo -r rules.trip
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr trip 1 ,
.Xr apsis 7
